race.comment: VENETIAN CHOICE (12) is a promising filly back from a 197-day spell. Showed pace but found one better over 1100m at Pakenham at her only appearance. Won a recent jump-out and this looks a lovely race for her return. JUSTIBELLA (9) closed well but found a couple better when favourite on debut at this track and distance 18 days ago. Will go back but should be powering home with the small field helping her cause. New Hayes acquisition CHERGUI (2) led but was overhauled as public elect when resuming at Seymour recently. Black type placegetter last prep who can improve off that run. JESSICA RABBIT (8) is on debut and has been kept very safe in early markets. Hard to imagine any of the other runners saluting.
